        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The coordinate system is vertically flipped from the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "layoutFragmentFrame"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " origin ({"
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "0"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ","
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "0"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "} is at the upper-left corner). The size should be larger than "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "layoutFragmentFrame.size"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". The origin could be in the negative coordinate since the rendering could stretch out of "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "layoutFragmentFrame"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". Only valid when "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "state"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " greater than "
            },
            {
